{{Infobox website | name = Qantara.de | logo = Qantara.de.png | logo_size = 200px | screenshot = [[File:Qantara.de screenshot.png|250px]]<!-- please don't update this image unless the layout is significantly changed--> | url = {{url|http://www.qantara.de/}} | alexa = {{increase}} 181,535 ({{as of|2015|2|13|alt=February 2015}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/Qantara.de |title= Qantara.de Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate= 2015-02-13 }}</ref><!--Updated monthly by OKBot.--> | commercial = No | type = [[Islamic World]]/[[International relations]] | registration = No | language = [[Arabic]],<ref name=DW_PR>{{cite web | url= http://dw.de/p/3UOp |title= A Virtual Bridge Between Europe and the Islamic World | publisher= Deutsche Welle | agency= |last= |first= |last2= |first2= |last3= |first3= |editor= |date= 7 February 2007 |accessdate= 16 April 2003 |quote= }}</ref> [[English language|English]],<ref name=DW_PR/> [[German language|German]],<ref name=DW_PR/> [[Turkish language|Turkish]]<ref>{{cite web | url= http://dw.de/p/9ow5 |title= Online Magazine "Qantara.de - Dialogue with the Islamic World" now also in Turkish | publisher= Deutsche Welle | agency= |last= |first= |last2= |first2= |last3= |first3= |editor= |date= 7 February 2007 |accessdate= 6 May 2015 |quote= }}</ref> | owner = German Federal Agency for Civic Education/[[Deutsche Welle]]/[[Goethe-Institut]]/German Institute for Foreign Cultural Relations | author = | editor = | launch date = March, 2003 | current status = Online }}
'''Qantara.de''' ({{lang-ar|قنطرة}} ''qanṭarah'', meaning "bridge") is an [[Internet portal]] in [[German language|German]], [[English language|English]], and [[Arabic]], designed to promote intercultural dialogue between the [[Western world|Western]] and [[Islamic world]]s.
The portal was founded on the initiative of the [[German Foreign Office]], in reaction to the crisis ridden developments in relations to Islamic cultures in the wake of the shock of the [[September 11 attacks]] in the USA. Online since March 2003, the platform is jointly run by the [[German Federal Agency for Civic Education|German Federal Agency for Civic Education (bpb)]], Germany’s international broadcaster [[Deutsche Welle]] (DW), the [[Goethe-Institut]] (GI) and the [[German Institute for Foreign Cultural Relations ]] (ifa), and is funded by the foreign office. The task of the joint dialogue project is to promote understanding between the various cultures, with the aim of combating ignorance and prejudice through knowledge.
The editorial team works to publish writing by [[Western world|Western]] and [[Islamic]] authors who seek open and respectful discussion of both commonalities and controversial subjects. These have included diverse contributors, like the Egyptian literary scholar [[Nasr Hamid Abu Zaid]], the German former diplomat and Muslim [[Murad Hofmann]], the Islam theologian [[Halima Krausen]], the conflict researcher [[Heiner Bielefeldt]] and the physicist [[Ernst Ulrich von Weizsäcker]].
